  "prompt": "Why am I blocked from asking questions under anonymous basis on Quora?",
  "response": "There can be several reasons why you might be blocked from asking questions anonymously on Quora:\n\n1. **User Policy Violations**: If you've violated Quora's policies or guidelines in the past, your ability to ask questions anonymously may be restricted.\n\n2. **Account Issues**: There may be issues with your account, such as being flagged for spam or inappropriate content.\n\n3. **Quora\u2019s Review Process**: Quora may have a review process in place that can temporarily restrict the ability to ask questions anonymously for certain accounts.\n\n4. **Technical Glitches**: Sometimes, technical issues or glitches can lead to problems with features like anonymous questioning.\n\n5. **Content Moderation**: Quora may limit anonymity for users who have previously posted content that goes against community standards.\n\nIf you're unsure about why you're blocked, you might consider reaching out to Quora's support or checking their help center for more specific information related to your account.",
